# Meetup Planner - API Credentials Template
#
# IMPORTANT: This is a template file. DO NOT store actual credentials here.
#
# For secure credential storage, see SECURITY.md for recommended methods:
# - macOS: Use Keychain (recommended)
# - Linux: Use Secret Service (recommended)
# - Windows: Use Credential Manager (recommended)
# - Fallback: Environment variables (less secure)

# ============================================================================
# REQUIRED API KEYS
# ============================================================================

# Brave Search API Key
# Get yours at: https://brave.com/search/api/
# Used for: Discovering events across the web
# Permissions needed: Search API access
# Rate limits: Depends on your plan
BRAVE_API_KEY=your-brave-api-key-here

# Firecrawl API Key
# Get yours at: https://firecrawl.dev/app/api-keys
# Used for: Scraping event details from web pages
# Permissions needed: Web scraping API access
# Rate limits: Depends on your plan
FIRECRAWL_API_KEY=your-firecrawl-api-key-here

# ============================================================================
# SECURITY BEST PRACTICES
# ============================================================================
#
# 1. NEVER commit this file with actual keys to version control
# 2. Use least-privilege keys (create keys specifically for this skill)
# 3. Rotate keys every 90 days
# 4. Monitor API usage dashboards for unexpected activity
# 5. Revoke keys immediately if compromised
#
# ============================================================================
# PREFERRED SETUP METHOD (macOS)
# ============================================================================
#
# Instead of using this file, store credentials in Keychain:
#
# security add-generic-password -a "$USER" \
#   -s "claude-meetup-planner-brave" \
#   -w "your-brave-api-key-here"
#
# security add-generic-password -a "$USER" \
#   -s "claude-meetup-planner-firecrawl" \
#   -w "your-firecrawl-api-key-here"
#
# Retrieve with:
# security find-generic-password -a "$USER" \
#   -s "claude-meetup-planner-brave" -w
#
# ============================================================================
# PREFERRED SETUP METHOD (Linux)
# ============================================================================
#
# Instead of using this file, store credentials in Secret Service:
#
# secret-tool store --label='Brave API Key for Meetup Planner' \
#   application claude-meetup-planner service brave-api
#
# secret-tool store --label='Firecrawl API Key for Meetup Planner' \
#   application claude-meetup-planner service firecrawl-api
#
# Retrieve with:
# secret-tool lookup application claude-meetup-planner service brave-api
#
# ============================================================================
# USING ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES (LESS SECURE)
# ============================================================================
#
# If you must use environment variables, add to your shell profile:
#
# # ~/.zshrc or ~/.bashrc
# export BRAVE_API_KEY="your-key-here"
# export FIRECRAWL_API_KEY="your-key-here"
#
# Then reload: source ~/.zshrc
#
# ============================================================================
# VERIFICATION
# ============================================================================
#
# Test that your keys are accessible:
#
# echo ${BRAVE_API_KEY:0:10}...  # Should show first 10 chars
# echo ${FIRECRAWL_API_KEY:0:10}...
#
# ============================================================================
